From 7c67821a5f5deca4fee82ff05a9fa442fbe6da3b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: patch <patch@local>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 19:23:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: remove star from Playable filter, rename best fit to
 best build with module tooltips, move role-fit sort to bottom as Beta
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- '★ Playable' -> 'Playable' in the faction dropdown.
- Every '(best fit)' stat sort label renamed to '(best build)' for
  clarity, and each is now tagged with the slot kind (engine/weapon/
  turret/shield) that actually drives the number. Hovering the value
  cell (grid card or list view) shows the specific module name(s) the
  computed best-build loadout assumed for that stat, e.g. 'Assumes:
  SPL S Combat Engine Mk4' — answers 'what does best fit even mean'
  directly instead of leaving it opaque.
- 'By role fit' optgroup moved from the top to the bottom of the sort
  dropdown and relabeled 'By role fit (Beta)', matching the Roles
  page's own beta framing.
---
 src/views/ShipBrowser.tsx | 101 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 72 insertions(+), 29 deletions(-)

